						               													<description>From the back of the box (translated from the original French):&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Catch all your favorite Pok&amp;eacute;mon and become the best Pok&amp;eacute;mon Trainer! The box of Pok&amp;eacute;mon: Les Champions de Hoenn contains four different card games to discover with your parents or your friends. You will be able to catch the most famous Pok&amp;eacute;mon of the Hoenn region, (but also Pok&amp;eacute;mon from other regions) and finally initiate your parents to the secrets of Pok&amp;eacute;mon!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Four games for the best trainers to play with your family or friends!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Les Champions de Hoenn box contains a deck of 60 cards and a reference poster. There 7 cards of each of 7 colors (Pok&amp;eacute;mon types), plus 18 gray Pok&amp;eacute;mon cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The four games you can play with these cards are:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Le jeu des familles (the family game). A variation of Go Fish for 3 to 5 players where your goal is to gather all the Pok&amp;eacute;mon of one color, asking for Pok&amp;eacute;mon by name.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Le memory-la chasse aux Pok&amp;eacute;mon (Memory-the hunt of Pok&amp;eacute;mon). A variation on the memory game for 2 to 4 players, where you try to uncover the 2 or 3 cards that represent a Pok&amp;eacute;mon and its evolutions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;La bataille-l'arene Pok&amp;eacute;mon (The battle-the Pok&amp;eacute;mon arena). A variation of War for 2 players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Le jeu du Pok&amp;eacute;dex (The Pok&amp;eacute;dex game). An original game for 2 to 6 players where you have to decide what cards to play in order to draw more cards, and which cards to keep for scoring at the end of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
